definition.value: Body substance in liquid state contained in the anterior and posterior chambers of the eyeball.
General anatomical term applied to nerves in which somatic efferent and/or somatic afferent nerve fibers predominate.
Body substance of semisolid state which constitutes the vitreous body of the eye.
Mucoid tissue in the vitreous chamber of the eyeball. Examples: There are only two instances, right and left vitreous bodies.
Vitreous humor which fills the canal occupied by the hyaloid artery.

Subdivision of neural tree (organ) which primarily consists of cell bodies of neurons located outside the neuraxis (brain and spinal cord); together with a nucleus and its associated nerve, it constitutes a neural tree (organ). Examples: spinal ganglion, trigeminal ganglion, superior cervical ganglion, celiac ganglion, inferior hypogastric (pelvic) ganglion.
